Figure 4g shows the reconfigurable rectifying behavior of the SJFET with different Vg in which the rectifying direction was switched by Vg. The maximum rectifying ratio reached 3×106 in the positive rectifying direction and 2.5 × 105 in the negative rectifying direction, whereas the rectifying ratio of the all-MGr-contacted WSe2 Schottky diode was only about 10 at Vds = ±1 V. To further evaluate the rectifying performance of the gate-tunable WSe2 Schottky junction diode, an ideality factor (n) was estimated at a small forward bias (here is 0.02–0.35 V) by fitting to Schottky diode Eq. (8).8Ids=IsexpVdsnVT−1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
