				\begin{document}$${I}_{{{{{\rm{ds}}}}}}={I}_{{{{{\rm{s}}}}}}\left[\exp \left(\frac{{V}_{{{{{\rm{ds}}}}}}}{n{V}_{{{{{\rm{T}}}}}}}-1\right)\right]$$\end{document}where Ids, Is, Vds, and VT denote the drain current, reverse leakage current, drain voltage, and thermal voltage, respectively. As the gate voltage swept from positive to negative in Fig. 4h, the ideality factor n derived from the parameters of the fitting equation was nearly fixed on 1 with negligible variation, indicating a near-ideal diode attribute in the reconfiguration process. Figure 4i summarizes the reported ideality factors and off-state current of the 2D SJFET, indicating the high quality of the asymmetric contacted SJFET and the application potential towards lower static power dissipation.
